not be spatially flat (i.e. $\\Omega_k \\ne 0$, even if in the early\nUniverse $\\Omega_k = 0$) and therefore when analysing low-$z$ cosmological data\none should keep $\\Omega_k$ as a free parameter and independent from the CMB\nconstraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Apr 2017 11:37:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 22 May 2017 08:33:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 13 Jun 2017 06:25:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-15"}
